# Vendored from https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/nixon-diamond/nixon-diamond.n3
# Unmodified besides dropping the trailing `log:impliesAnswer` query line
# (this engine has no query/goal-extraction mechanism -- see main.rs, this
# suite only ever runs full materialize() and checks derived facts).
#
# BLOCKED (see nixon_diamond_result.n3 / manifest.json "status": "ignored"):
# this is a *rule-priority* example -- Rule 2 (Republicans are NonPacifist)
# is supposed to fire before Rule 1 (Quakers are Pacifist, guarded by
# `log:notIncludes { ?x a ex:NonPacifist }`) so the SNAF guard can see the
# NonPacifist fact and block Rule 1. This crate's `Reasoner::materialize`
# evaluates every rule in a stratum against one shared per-iteration
# TripleIndex snapshot and only merges all rules' newly-derived triples into
# the store in a single batch *after* the whole iteration finishes (see the
# `new_triples_in_loop` accumulator in reasoner.rs) -- there is no rule
# priority/ordering concept, so a `log:notIncludes` guard in one rule can
# never observe a fact asserted by another rule of the same stratum within
# the same fixpoint iteration. Both `ex:Pacifist` and `ex:NonPacifist` get
# derived simultaneously instead of only `ex:NonPacifist`.
@prefix log: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#> .
@prefix ex:  <http://example.org/nixon#> .

ex:RichardNixon  a ex:Quaker, ex:Republican .

{ ?x a ex:Quaker .
  ?SCOPE log:notIncludes { ?x a ex:NonPacifist } .
}  =>  { ?x a ex:Pacifist } .

{ ?x a ex:Republican }  =>  { ?x a ex:NonPacifist } .
